"The vacuum created by the lack of facts", noted Mr. Englund, "was filled with conjectures, assumptions, hopes, fears, prejudices, conspiracy theories, dreams, nightmares, and rumors".
Beauty and Sorrow follows the stories of individuals such as Florence Farmborough, an English nurse in the Russian army, and Richard Stumpf, a young sailor serving in the German navy.
Their stories are entirely taken from biographies, letters, and other published material.
