The government of the large coalition of Social Democrats and Christian Democrats in power in Austria decided on Tuesday to write the "golden rule" of fiscal policy into the constitution in order to reduce the public deficit and thus avoid any reduction in the rating of Austria by the rating agencies (AAA).
